{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9b25a8ad-539f-456f-ab24-cdfa8fc28a0c","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` — enables `dotnet test` integration on .NET 8\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\nAlso set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in your test `.csproj` so `dotnet test` delegates to the new platform. Arguments after `--` are forwarded to the MTP runner.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"abc9a58f-79c7-4ed5-9f43-e5a874248e0a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same, but may need `--treenode-filter` for the new filter syntax)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you use a different mechanism\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nNow I'm realizing the Microsoft.Testing.Platform CLI syntax differs more significantly than I initially thought. The filter syntax needs adjustment—`--treenode-filter` uses a different format than the old `--filter` with Category=Integration, and I'll need to check if the VSTest bridge supports the legacy filter syntax. For TRX reporting, I need the Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport package, and code coverage requires a different approach with Microsoft.CodeCoverage.\n\nFor crash and hang dumps, the new flags are `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with their respective timeout options, each requiring specific extension packages. The execution method is flexible—I can still use `dotnet test` with arguments passed after `--`, or run the test app directly with `dotnet exec` or as a standalone executable. With .NET 9 SDK and later, `dotnet test` has native support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform, which simplifies things.\n\nFor .NET 8, I have a few options: use `dotnet test` with the VSTest bridge via Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild (by setting `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in the project file), run the test executable directly, or use `dotnet run`. The MSBuild integration is the recommended approach since it lets me keep using `dotnet test` even on older frameworks.\n\nWhen passing Microsoft.Testing.Platform arguments with the MSBuild integration, I need to put them after `--` in the command. So I'd structure it as `dotnet test -- <MTP args>` rather than passing them directly to `dotnet test`. The specific filter syntax and argument format depends on how the testing platform is configured in the project.","outputTokens":1419,"requestId":"0842:307F5D:814FB61:8F7E7CB:69EABE7A"},"id":"4905d983-3448-47a4-9a42-c4fa6ea7e4ef","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:33.128Z","parentId":"18fbc075-06e4-484e-93ce-7d0fcb1388c3"}
